results.name: Maximum rectangle of partitions in Abramowitz and Stegun order.
link: M. Abramowitz and I. A. Stegun, eds., Handbook of Mathematical Functions, National Bureau of Standards, Applied Math. Series 55, Tenth Printing, 1972 [alternative scanned copy].
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Ferrers Diagram.
example: Partition 33 in A&S order is [4,3]; its maximum rectangle is 2x3 = 6, so a(33)=6.
results.author: _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Mar 11 2006
